  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "HR Executive (Infrastructure Industry)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Our client is a well-established construction, property development and specialist engineering\nsolutions provider. Currently, they are currently seeking for HR Executive to be part of HR team.</strong></p><p><strong>The Human Resource Executive will manage the full spectrum of HR functions, with a primary focus on end-to-end recruitment activities. This role supports the organization’s manpower needs by attracting, selecting, and retaining suitable talent, while ensuring HR operations comply with company policies and statutory requirements.</strong><br /></p><p><strong>JOB DIMENSION (SCOPE)</strong></p><ul><li>Manage end-to-end recruitment activities including sourcing, interviewing, and onboarding</li><li>Coordinate with hiring managers on manpower planning and hiring needs</li><li>Administer employee records and support HR operations across the employee lifecycle</li><li>Handle work pass applications and ensure compliance with MOM regulations</li><li>Support leave administration, and HR documentation</li><li>Assist in employee relations, engagement activities, and policy implementation</li><li>Perform other HR-related duties as assigned</li></ul><p><br /><strong>JOB REQUIREMENTS</strong></p><ul><li>Experience in using Easypay will be advantageous (not mandatory)</li><li>Diploma / Degree in Human Resource Management, Business Administration, or related field</li><li>2–5 years of HR experience, preferably with strong recruitment exposure</li><li>Hands-on experience in end-to-end recruitment</li><li>Knowledge of Singapore employment laws and MOM regulations</li><li>Experience handling work passes is an advantage</li><li>Good communication, coordination, and organizational skills</li><li>Able to work independently and manage multiple hiring priorities</li></ul><p><br />Onion Search Pte Ltd</p><p>EA License No: 24C2108</p><p>EA Personnel: Clover Lai Kah Wai</p><p>EA Personnel No: R24120119</p>",
